---

### Why these are important:

*   **`.vs/` and `.vscode/`**: These store your personal window layouts, open tabs, and local debug settings. Committing these often causes "merge noise" for other team members.
*   **`.terraform/`**: This folder can be several hundred megabytes because it holds the compiled binaries for the Azure DevOps provider. It should always be recreated by running `terraform init`.
*   **`*.tfstate`**: **This is the most critical.** Terraform state files often store your `ado_pat` in plain text. If you push this to a public (or even private) repo, your credentials are compromised.
*   **`*.tfvars`**: Since you are using this to store your `ado_pat` and `ado_org_url` locally, keeping it out of Git is your primary line of defense.

### Pro-Tip for Senior Engineers
Since you are working with multiple tools, you can use a service like **[gitignore.io](https://www.toptal.com/developers/gitignore/api/visualstudio,terraform,windows)** to generate a combined file. 

If you have already accidentally committed one of these files (like the `.terraform` folder), Git will continue to track it even after you add it to `.gitignore`. You’ll need to "untackFor a **Visual Studio** environment (specifically when working with Terraform and Azure), your `.gitignore` needs to cover three main areas: the IDE’s own "junk" files, Terraform's state/provider files, and sensitive credential files.

Here is a standard, robust list to use. You can create a file named `.gitignore` in your project root and paste this in:
```text
# === Visual Studio / VS Code ===
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
bin/
obj/

# === Terraform ===
# Local .terraform folder (contains providers and modules)
.terraform/

# State files (contain sensitive data and plain-text secrets)
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.backup
*.tfstate.lock.info
terraform.tfvars

# Crash logs
crash.log
crash.*.log

# === Sensitive Secrets (Crucial!) ===
# Personal Access Tokens and Org URLs
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json

# Environment files
.env
.env.local

# === Windows / System ===
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/